# DesignSpark — testing rules

## Tools
- Unit tests: JUnit 4 + MockK + Turbine (Flow testing)
- Instrumented tests: JUnit 4 + Room in-memory database
- Never use Mockito — use MockK exclusively

## Coverage expectations
- Domain layer (use cases): 100% — these are pure Kotlin, no excuses
- Data layer (repository): happy path + error path for every public method
- ViewModel layer: loading → success and loading → error for every screen
- DAOs: insert, query, delete for all three entities

## ViewModel test pattern

```kotlin
@OptIn(ExperimentalCoroutinesApi::class)
class HomeViewModelTest {
    @get:Rule val mainDispatcherRule = MainDispatcherRule()

    private val getProjects: GetProjectsUseCase = mockk()
    private lateinit var viewModel: HomeViewModel

    @Test
    fun `uiState emits projects on success`() = runTest {
        val projects = listOf(/* test data */)
        every { getProjects() } returns flowOf(projects)
        viewModel = HomeViewModel(getProjects)

        viewModel.uiState.test {
            val state = awaitItem()
            assertThat(state.projects).isEqualTo(projects)
            assertThat(state.isLoading).isFalse()
        }
    }
}
```

## Repository test pattern — mock the API, verify Room

```kotlin
@Test
fun `generateCompetitors writes results to Room on success`() = runTest {
    val mockApi = mockk<OpenAiApiService>()
    coEvery { mockApi.sendMessage(any()) } returns validCompetitorResponse()

    repository.generateCompetitors(testProject)

    val saved = competitorDao.getByProjectId(testProject.id).first()
    assertThat(saved).hasSize(3)
    assertThat(saved.first().type).isEqualTo(InsightType.COMPETITOR.name)
}
```

## DAO test pattern — always use in-memory database

```kotlin
@RunWith(AndroidJUnit4::class)
class ProjectDaoTest {
    private lateinit var db: AppDatabase
    private lateinit var dao: ProjectDao

    @Before
    fun setup() {
        db = Room.inMemoryDatabaseBuilder(
            ApplicationProvider.getApplicationContext(),
            AppDatabase::class.java
        ).allowMainThreadQueries().build()
        dao = db.projectDao()
    }

    @After
    fun teardown() = db.close()
}
```

## What to test for chained AI calls specifically
The SWOT generation has a dependency on competitor data existing in Room.
Always write a test for the failure case:

```kotlin
@Test
fun `generateSwot returns failure when no competitor data exists`() = runTest {
    // Do not insert any competitor data
    val result = repository.generateSwot(testProjectId)
    assertThat(result.isFailure).isTrue()
}
```
